### <a id="1-18-0-breaking-changes"></a>Breaking Changes

<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> v1.18.0 includes the following breaking changes:  

* **SecurityContextDeny Admission Controller Support Has Been Removed**: 
Support for SecurityContextDeny admission controller has been removed in <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> v1.18. 
You must deactivate SecurityContextDeny in all active Plans before upgrading to <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> v1.18.  

    The SecurityContextDeny admission controller has been deprecated, and the Kubernetes community recommends the controller not be used. 
    For more information, see [Deactivate the SecurityContextDeny Admission Controller](checklist.html#securitycontextdeny) in _Upgrade Preparation Checklist for <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>_.  

    Pod security admission (PSA) is the preferred method for providing a more secure Kubernetes environment. 
    For more information about PSA, see [Pod Security Admission in <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>](pod-security-admission.html).  

* **Telegraf has been upgraded for host monitoring**: 
Telegraf has been upgraded to Telegraf v1.28.1 for host monitoring.  

    Previous <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> versions have used Telegraf v1.20.3 for host monitoring. 
    For information on the differences between the Telegraf v1.20.3 and v1.28.1 releases, 
    see [Telegraf v1.28.1](https://docs.influxdata.com/telegraf/v1.28/about_the_project/release-notes-changelog/) 
    and [Telegraf v1.24.0 Breaking Change](https://docs.influxdata.com/telegraf/v1/release-notes-changelog/#v1240-2022-09-12) in the Telegraf Release Notes documentation.  
<% if vars.product_version == "COMMENTED"  %>
    <p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> Cluster monitoring continues to use Telegraf v1.13.2.
    </p>
